      "question": "Using Euclid's division algorithm, find the Highest Common Factor (HCF) of $135$ and $225$.",
      "answer": "$45$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Apply Euclid's division lemma to $225$ and $135$ to express as $225 = 135 \\times 1 + 90$.",
          "Apply the lemma to the divisor $135$ and remainder $90$ to get $135 = 90 \\times 1 + 45$.",
          "Apply the lemma to $90$ and $45$ to get $90 = 45 \\times 2 + 0$. Since the remainder is $0$, the divisor $45$ is the HCF."
        ],
        "derivation": "$225 = 135 \\times 1 + 90 \\\\ 135 = 90 \\times 1 + 45 \\\\ 90 = 45 \\times 2 + 0 \\\\ \\therefore \\text{HCF}(225, 135) = 45$"
      },
